PC Number Date Chapter Bill Dept
 1999-04821999-03-190,  ,  FAIT,  , 
PrecisAppointment of CLAUDE BAILLARGEON as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Central African Republic and the Republic of Chad, with residence in Yaoundé; JAMES K. BARTLEMAN as High Commissioner for Canada to the Kingdom of Lesotho and the Kingdom of Swaziland, with residence in Pretoria; DENIS BRIAND as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Sierra Leone, with residence in Conakry; GERALD K. CAMPBELL as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Rwandese Republic, and the Republic of Burundi, with residence in Nairobi; JANET GRAHAM as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Benin, with residence in Accra; JEREMY KINSMAN as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Albania, with residence in Rome; CLAUDE LAVERDURE as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg, with residence in Brussels; JOHN NOBLE as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Principality of Liechtenstein, with residence in Berne; and JOHN SCHRAM as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Djibouti, and to Eritrea, with residence in Addis Ababa.
